comments: Porter Jr. (GSW) is already in Primo's (SAS) path and marginal contact occurs as Primo moves toward the wing to defend the drive.
Wiggins (GSW) is already in Vassell's (SAS) path and absorbs the marginal contact that occurs following the hand-off.
Richardson (SAS) brings his hand toward Kuminga's (GSW) side and marginal contact occurs as Kuminga elevates for the layup attempt.
Kuminga (GSW) brings his left arm forward and marginal contact occurs with Murray's (SAS) right arm as Murray spins inside the perimeter.
Kuminga (GSW) briefly has his arm around Johnson's (SAS) midsection before correcting.
Johnson (SAS) firms up in his screening position in Kuminga's (GSW) path and absorbs the contact.
Primo (SAS) brings his left hand toward Wiggins' (GSW) side and marginal contact occurs as Wiggins elevates to pass.
Primo (SAS) brings his forearm toward Wiggins' (GSW) back and marginal contact occurs as they each attempt to establish rebounding position.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Wiggins (GSW) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Kuminga (GSW) brings his hand toward Murray's (SAS) hip and marginal contact occurs as Murray passes the ball at the end of the drive.
Murray (SAS) and Porter Jr. (GSW) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.

Johnson (SAS) brushes Poole's (GSW) right arm and Poole is able to move through the marginal contact to finish at the rim. Simultaneously, Murray (SAS) brings his forearm toward Poole's path and marginal contact occurs with Poole's front during the driving shot attempt.
Johnson (SAS) firms up in his screening position in Kuminga's (GSW) path and absorbs the contact as the defensive switch takes place.

Wiggins (GSW) brings his left hand outward and marginal contact occurs with Murray's (SAS) right arm and side after Murray's gather. Kuminga (GSW) attempts to jump vertically as he contests the driving shot attempt and absorbs a majority of the contact as Murray drifts toward the baseline during the follow-through. There is slight forward movement by Kuminga and the body contact is deemed marginal.
Porter Jr. (GSW) and Vassell (SAS) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Vassell (SAS) commits a take foul on Poole (GSW).
After initially engaging with one another, Poeltl (SAS) brings his hand toward Kuminga's (GSW) front and quickly removes it without grabbing Kuminga's jersey.
Porter Jr. (GSW) and Johnson (SAS) engage and disengage with one another as they each attempt to establish rebounding position.
Kuminga (GSW) saves the ball back into play prior to his foot landing out of bounds.
Vassell (SAS) initiates contact across Wiggins' (GSW) right shoulder as Wiggins starts his dribble and then uses both hands to grab Wiggins' hips after he re-gains control of the ball.
Looney (GSW) holds Poeltl's (SAS) left shoulder during the rebound and the contact affects his FOM.
Murray (SAS) extends his arm in pursuit of the rebound and incidental arm contact occurs with Thompson (GSW) and Wiggins (GSW) as the ball ricochets away.
Johnson (SAS) and Porter Jr. (GSW) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Porter Jr. (GSW) legally contests Johnson's (SAS) put-back attempt.
Bjelica (GSW) slightly extends outward as he sets the screen on Johnson (SAS) and Bjelica absorbs the contact.
